    <h2 class="eng-h2">Engage vs traditional</h2>
    <div class="eng-rule"></div>
    <p class="eng-lead" style="margin-bottom:18px;">Same job. Different way of grading it. This isn't about traditional methods being wrong — it's about where Engage differs, and why some organisations find it more practical in fast-changing environments.</p>
    <p class="in-short"><strong>In short:</strong> traditional methods often prioritise formality and documentation. Engage prioritises practical role understanding, transparency, and usability — without asking organisations to give up rigour.</p>
    <button class="toggle" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="compare-panel" onclick="toggleCompare(this)"><span class="label">See the full side-by-side</span><span class="chev">▼</span></button>
    <div class="panel" id="compare-panel">
      <div class="panel-pad">
        <div class="tbl-wrap">
          <table>
            <thead><tr><td>Dimension</td><td class="eng">Engage</td><td>Traditional approaches</td></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
<tr><td class="area">Starting point</td><td class="eng">Uses role descriptions as reference, but direct role knowledge is central</td><td class="trad">Relies heavily on job descriptions and indirect documentation</td></tr>
<tr><td class="area">Methodology</td><td class="eng">Factor-based, using five evaluation grids and structured judgement</td><td class="trad">Structured, but often specialist-heavy and process-intensive</td></tr>
<tr><td class="area">Role knowledge in the room</td><td class="eng">Knowledgeable people, including incumbents, participate directly</td><td class="trad">Often limited or excluded — committees rely on second-hand information</td></tr>
<tr><td class="area">Speed of use</td><td class="eng">Designed to be fast — “5 judgements, 5 minutes” as a working principle</td><td class="trad">Can be slow, time-intensive, and bureaucratic</td></tr>
<tr><td class="area">Ease of explanation</td><td class="eng">Transparent and visible — judgements are made openly and practically</td><td class="trad">Logic can be hard for non-specialists to follow and defend</td></tr>
<tr><td class="area">Dependency on consultants</td><td class="eng">Designed to build internal ownership and capability over time</td><td class="trad">Often highly dependent on external or specialist evaluators</td></tr>
