        <div class="prose">
          <div class="p1"><h3>The role of job descriptions</h3><p>Traditional methods often place the job description at the centre of the evaluation. Engage treats it differently — useful as a reference point, but not the foundation. Job descriptions are often incomplete, outdated, or shaped by whoever wrote them, and in fast-changing organisations they lag behind the reality of the role quickly. Engage reduces over-dependence on the document and increases reliance on informed role knowledge and structured judgement.</p></div>
          <div class="p2"><h3>Direct vs indirect knowledge</h3><p>Indirect evaluation carries risk — the role can be misunderstood, the description biased, the outcome inaccurate. Engage brings direct knowledge into the room instead, improving accuracy, speed of clarification, and trust in the result.</p></div>
          <div class="p3"><h3>What makes a methodology easy to maintain</h3><p>Understandable, transparent, fast enough to use, and not overly dependent on external specialists. Engage is designed to support ongoing resizing and committee use — a living governance process, not a once-off exercise.</p></div>
